cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image denoising using fluorescence microscopy images. The use of deep learning methods also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and machine learning applications (cs.LG) sub-categories. Information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) could also be possible sub-categories as they deal with image processing and optimization, which are relevant to the denoising algorithms used in this paper.
